│  This script is intended to serve as a basic example of how one might        │
│  implement a path traversal vulnerability scanner. The class                 │
│  `PathTraversalScanner` provides the functionality for detecting potential   │
│  paths leading outside a permitted directory structure, typically in         │
│  web-application context but not specifically tied to any application        │
│  framework. The code includes static methods such as `is_valid_path()` for   │
│  validation purposes and dynamic ones, including a simplified `scan()`       │
│  method aimed at identifying possible path traversal vulnerabilities based   │
│  on a regular expression pattern. The main function (`main()`) demonstrates  │
│  how the scanner can be used along with some example paths that could        │
│  represent potential security issues.                                        │
