│      scanner._errors.append(f"Could not process {element_tree} as it         │
│  contains an external reference.")                                           │
│                                                                              │
│      assert                                                                  │
│  scanner.scan_xml_from_url('http://example.com/data.xml')['Errors']          │
│      print("Scanner Setup is Correct and Test passed!")                      │
│  ```                                                                         │
│                                                                              │
│  This code implements the XXE (XML External Entity) Scanner. It uses         │
│  `requests` to fetch content, then parses XML with `xml.etree.ElementTree`.  │
│  It checks for XXE by looking for any tokens like `{}` or `"%" e="`, which   │
│  are indicative of an external entity being used.                            │
│                                                                              │
│  The `_find_external_reference` method iterates through all child nodes and  │
│  tags in the XML structure checking if they reference other documents. If a  │
│  token indicating an external reference is found, it adds the error message  │
│  to `_errors`.                                                               │
│                                                                              │
│  The `scan_xml_from_url` function does a GET request on the provided URL,    │
│  parses this content into an ElementTree with `_find_external_reference`,    │
│  handles any errors or issues, and returns information about detected XXE    │
│  tokens if any are encountered.                                              │
│                                                                              │
│  Finally, we have assertions as part of the main block for testing to        │
│  ensure that at least one error is returned from scanning a dummy content.   │
│  The `scan_xml_from_url` function can only be called directly in production  │
│  as it will expose vulnerabilities while still being able to verify          │
│  correctness via assertions or unit tests.                                   │
│                                                                              │
│                                                                              │
